# Walkthrough: Homepage Performance Optimization

I have implemented several significant optimizations to improve the Scrolli homepage performance, specifically targeting Time to First Byte (TTFB), image orchestration, and environment stability.

## Content Fixes: Defensive Filtering

I have identified that several articles on the homepage were missing content or images due to "Zombie" entries in the CMS (published articles with incomplete data or broken media links).

### Broken Articles Identified
1.  **Devlerin yapay zekâ...** (Gündem): Published version has empty content and broken images. A valid version exists in Drafts.
2.  **Sam Rivers of Limp Bizkit dies** (Alara AI): The article exists in the `alaraai` collection but references a media ID (`6994ff2804667506d7693ccb`) that no longer exists in the CMS.

### Fix implemented
I have implemented a **Defensive Filtering** system on the homepage ([homepage.ts](file:///Users/FAU1MU/development/Vscode%20Projects/Scrolli/scrolli-website-project/lib/homepage.ts)). The [isValidArticle](file:///Users/FAU1MU/development/Vscode%20Projects/Scrolli/scrolli-website-project/lib/homepage.ts#26-63) helper now ensures:
- **Content Check**: Articles must have either structured content (Lexical JSON) or an Inline Script (used by **Hikayeler** and **Stories**) to be displayed.
- **Media Check**: All articles (including **Hikayeler**, **Gündem**, **Alara AI**, **Stories**, etc.) must have a valid, expanded image object with a URL. If only an ID (string) is returned, it means the media link is broken, and the article is hidden.

This fix prevents these "zombie" articles from appearing on the UI even if the CMS data is incomplete.

## Performance Improvements

### 1. Parallelized Data Fetching
Previously, the homepage fetched content sequentially, leading to a "Waterfall" effect that contributed to a high TTFB (5.6s). I have refactored [lib/homepage.ts](file:///Users/FAU1MU/development/Vscode%20Projects/Scrolli/scrolli-website-project/lib/homepage.ts) and [app/page.tsx](file:///Users/FAU1MU/development/Vscode%20Projects/Scrolli/scrolli-website-project/app/page.tsx) to fire all primary API requests concurrently using `Promise.all`.

- **Impact**: Significant reduction in server-side processing time.

### 2. Image Optimization (Resolution Fix)
To prevent the loading of 4K assets for small thumbnails, I have updated the `sizes` attribute in all major homepage sections.

- **Optimized Files**:
  - [HeroSection.tsx](file:///Users/FAU1MU/development/Vscode%20Projects/Scrolli/scrolli-website-project/components/sections/home/HeroSection.tsx)
  - [Section1.tsx](file:///Users/FAU1MU/development/Vscode%20Projects/Scrolli/scrolli-website-project/components/sections/home/Section1.tsx)
  - [Section3.tsx](file:///Users/FAU1MU/development/Vscode%20Projects/Scrolli/scrolli-website-project/components/sections/home/Section3.tsx)

### 3. Stability & TTFB (ISR Integration)
I have refactored [page.tsx](file:///Users/FAU1MU/development/Vscode%20Projects/Scrolli/scrolli-website-project/app/page.tsx) to move from a "force-dynamic" SSR model to an **ISR (Incremental Static Regeneration)** model with a 60-second revalidation period.

## Verification Results

### Automated Performance Audit
- [x] Sequential awaits removed.
- [x] Section 3 Waterfall eliminated.
- [x] Hero image `priority` and `sizes` corrected.
- [x] "Zombie" articles filtered out from the homepage.
